author: Brian Johnson
title: MnDOT still paying for 2011 shutdown
text: Home / News / Construction & Development / MnDOT still paying for 2011 shutdown The Minnesota Department of Transportation has made roughly $2.49 million worth of interim payments to contractors on the Highway 61 Hastings bridge project since the state government shutdown in 2011. (File photo: Bill Klotz) MnDOT still paying for 2011 shutdown By: Brian Johnson July 2, 2015 7:04 am 0 Costs of the July 2011 shutdown may go higher still, as MnDOT is still negotiating with an handful of contractors.
